/-! # Per-pair LipSDP scorecard, FULL 784-dim input — unconstrained net (`mlpTF`)

The tighter-Lipschitz-constant pass over the SAME first-100 MNIST test
subset as `LipschitzCertScorecardFull.lean`, at BOTH ε = 1/10 and 3/10:
per-pair LipSDP constants lift the counts from **76→91/100 @ ε=0.1**
(PGD bracket 94) and **2→77/100 @ ε=0.3** (PGD 86) — no
retraining, no new data, a less lossy constant per pairwise logit gap.

Everything pair-level is hidden-width-sized (16×16, Schur — the 784-dim
input never appears); the PSD witness is an exact rational LDLᵀ, checked
as one `linarith` goal per pair from the column squares (`hS*` — measured
faster than the entrywise `lipsdp_slack_of_cert` route at both widths).
The 784-term work — Gram wrappers `G1*_eq`, the per-image `hpre*_eval` —
is reused from the kernel-dotZ scorecard files.

Generated by `scripts/lipschitz_cert_pair_sdp_full.py`; weights/images/
certificates are DATA (SDP solved off-line, verified exactly here). -/

